The pouches market can be analyzed on the basis of material type, product type, and closure type. Material type segmentation includes plastic, metal, paper, and others. Plastic pouches are extensively used in various industries due to their flexibility, durability, and cost-effectiveness. Metal pouches, on the other hand, offer high barrier properties making them suitable for packaging sensitive products. Paper pouches are preferred for their eco-friendly nature. Product type segmentation consists of stand-up pouches, flat pouches, roll pouches, retort pouches, and others. Stand-up pouches are convenient for storage and display, while flat pouches are commonly used for single-serving products. Closure type segmentation includes zippers, spouts, tear notch, valves, and others, each offering unique functionalities for different packaging needs.

